      "source": [
        "# Query to Drug Candidate in Minutes\n",
        "### with Activeloop's Deep Lake on AWS Sagemaker Lakehouse\n",
        "\n",
        "Tapping into the multimodal data for drug discovery, Scientists can shortlist first-in-class candidates in minutes instead of days.\n",
        "\n",
        "Life & Science companies have 20 years of assay tables, microscopy images, genomic sequences, and full-text literature. Most of this data is siloed costing slow time to market for drugs.\n",
        "\n",
        "In this example, we take open datasets like PubMed articles, ChEMBL/PubChem assays, GenBank sequences, and public high-content imaging sets to demostrate how you can unify and index multimodal data on your Sagemaker Lakehouse with Deep Lake.   \n",
        "\n",
        "Furthermore, we leverage Deep Lake's index-on-the-lake technology to enable AI Search directly within the Lakehouse, leveraging  \n",
        "- 1️⃣  Lexical:  “IL-17 inhibitor IC50 < 10 nM”)\n",
        "- 2️⃣  Semantic: “compounds that produce ‘zebrafish heart-looping’ phenotype” across images\n",
        "- 3️⃣  Visual Search: context-aware ranking by disease pathway and toxicity profiles\n",
        "\n",
        "Presented by AWS and Activeloop"
      ]
    },

      "source": [
        "def create_pubchem_assay_table(ds_name: str, retmax: int = 100) -> deeplake.Dataset:\n",
        "    schema = {\n",
        "        'aid': \"int32\",\n",
        "        'title': Text(index_type=BM25),\n",
        "        'description': Text(index_type=BM25),\n",
        "        'payload': Dict(),\n",
        "    }\n",
        "\n",
        "    if deeplake.exists(ds_name):\n",
        "        ds = deeplake.delete(ds_name)\n",
        "\n",
        "    ds = deeplake.create(ds_name, schema=schema)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Get all assay IDs\n",
        "    q = {\n",
        "        'db': 'pcassay',\n",
        "        'term': 'all[filt]',      # returns every live PubChem BioAssay ID\n",
        "        'retmax': retmax,\n",
        "        'retmode': 'json'\n",
        "    }\n",
        "    ids = requests.get(\n",
        "            'https://eutils.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/eutils/esearch.fcgi',\n",
        "            params=q\n",
        "        ).json()['esearchresult']['idlist']\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Get all assay metadata\n",
        "    for aid in tqdm(ids):\n",
        "        r = requests.get(f'https://pubchem.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/rest/pug/assay/aid/{aid}/JSON')\n",
        "        if r.ok:\n",
        "            assay = r.json().get('PC_AssaySubmit', {}).get('assay').get('descr')\n",
        "            aid = aid\n",
        "            title = assay.get('name')\n",
        "            description = assay.get('description')\n",
        "            ds.append([{\n",
        "                'aid': int(aid),\n",
        "                'title': title,\n",
        "                'description': ' '.join(description),\n",
        "                'payload': assay\n",
        "            }])\n",
        "    ds.commit()\n",
        "    return ds\n",
        "\n",
        "pubchem = create_pubchem_assay_table(f\"{lakehouse_s3}/pubchem_assays\", retmax = 100)\n",
        "pubchem.summary()"
      ]
    },

    },
    {
      "cell_type": "code",
      "execution_count": null,
      "id": "13241cd4-228f-4b47-a79d-0f26d3be7c23",

        "execution": {

        "id": "13241cd4-228f-4b47-a79d-0f26d3be7c23",

      },
      "outputs": [
        {
          "name": "stdout",
          "output_type": "stream",
          "text": [
            "Generating embeddings...\n",
            "1024\n"
          ]
        }
      ],
      "source": [
        "import boto3\n",
        "import base64\n",
        "import json\n",
        "import os\n",
        "from PIL import Image\n",
        "import io\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "class TitanEmbeddingGenerator():\n",
        "    def __init__(self, region_name='us-east-1'):\n",
        "        \"\"\"Initialize the Titan Embedding Generator with AWS Bedrock client.\"\"\"\n",
        "        self.bedrock_runtime = boto3.client('bedrock-runtime', region_name=region_name)\n",
        "        self.image_model_id = 'amazon.titan-embed-image-v1'\n",
        "        self.text_model_id = 'amazon.titan-embed-image-v1'\n",
        "\n",
        "    def generate_embeddings(self, img=None, text=None, output_length=1024):\n",
        "        \"\"\"\n",
        "        Generate embeddings for an image, text, or both using Amazon Titan embedding models\n",
        "\n",
        "        Args:\n",
        "            image_path (str, optional): Path to the image file\n",
        "            text (str, optional): Text input to embed\n",
        "            output_length (int): Desired embedding length (default: 1024)\n",
        "\n",
        "        Returns:\n",
        "            dict: Dictionary containing embeddings and metadata\n",
        "        \"\"\"\n",
        "        if not img and not text:\n",
        "            raise ValueError(\"At least one of image_path or text must be provided\")\n",
        "\n",
        "        results = {}\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Process image if provided\n",
        "        if img:\n",
        "            image_embedding = self._generate_image_embedding(img, output_length)\n",
        "            results['image_embedding'] = image_embedding\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Process text if provided\n",
        "        if text:\n",
        "            text_embedding = self._generate_text_embedding(text, output_length)\n",
        "            results['text_embedding'] = text_embedding\n",
        "\n",
        "        return results\n",
        "\n",
        "    def _generate_image_embedding(self, img, output_length):\n",
        "        \"\"\"Generate embeddings for an image using Titan Embed Image model.\"\"\"\n",
        "        # Process the image\n",
        "        try:\n",
        "            # If image is very large, resize it to reduce payload size\n",
        "            max_size = 1024  # Maximum dimension\n",
        "            if max(img.size) > max_size:\n",
        "                ratio = max_size / max(img.size)\n",
        "                new_size = (int(img.size[0] * ratio), int(img.size[1] * ratio))\n",
        "                img = img.resize(new_size, Image.LANCZOS)\n",
        "\n",
        "            # Save to bytes\n",
        "            buffer = io.BytesIO()\n",
        "            img.save(buffer, format=img.format if img.format else 'JPEG')\n",
        "            image_bytes = buffer.getvalue()\n",
        "        except Exception as e:\n",
        "            raise Exception(f\"Error processing image: {str(e)}\")\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Encode the image as base64\n",
        "        encoded_image = base64.b64encode(image_bytes).decode('utf-8')\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Prepare the request body\n",
        "        request_body = {\n",
        "            \"inputImage\": encoded_image,\n",
        "            \"embeddingConfig\": {\n",
        "                \"outputEmbeddingLength\": output_length\n",
        "            }\n",
        "        }\n",
        "\n",
        "        try:\n",
        "            # Invoke the model\n",
        "            response = self.bedrock_runtime.invoke_model(\n",
        "                modelId=self.image_model_id,\n",
        "                body=json.dumps(request_body)\n",
        "            )\n",
        "\n",
        "            # Parse the response\n",
        "            response_body = json.loads(response['body'].read())\n",
        "            return response_body['embedding']\n",
        "\n",
        "        except Exception as e:\n",
        "            print(f\"Error generating image embedding: {str(e)}\")\n",
        "            return None\n",
        "\n",
        "    def _generate_text_embedding(self, text, output_length):\n",
        "        \"\"\"Generate embeddings for text using Titan Embed Text model.\"\"\"\n",
        "        # Prepare the request body\n",
        "        if len(text) > 5000:\n",
        "            text=text[:5000]\n",
        "\n",
        "        request_body = {\n",
        "            \"inputText\": text,\n",
        "            \"embeddingConfig\": {\n",
        "                \"outputEmbeddingLength\": output_length\n",
        "            }\n",
        "        }\n",
        "\n",
        "        try:\n",
        "            # Invoke the model\n",
        "            response = self.bedrock_runtime.invoke_model(\n",
        "                modelId=self.text_model_id,\n",
        "                body=json.dumps(request_body)\n",
        "            )\n",
        "\n",
        "            # Parse the response\n",
        "            response_body = json.loads(response['body'].read())\n",
        "            return response_body['embedding']\n",
        "\n",
        "        except Exception as e:\n",
        "            print(f\"Error generating text embedding: {str(e)}\")\n",
        "            return None\n",
        "\n",
        "# Initialize the embedding generator\n",
        "generator = TitanEmbeddingGenerator()\n",
        "text = \"This is an example text to generate embeddings for\"\n",
        "\n",
        "# Generate embeddings\n",
        "print(\"Generating embeddings...\")\n",
        "results = generator.generate_embeddings(text=text)\n",
        "print(len(results['text_embedding']))"
      ]
    },

      "source": [
        "import requests, xml.etree.ElementTree as ET, deeplake\n",
        "from deeplake.types import Text, BM25, Dict, Embedding\n",
        "\n",
        "def create_pubmed_table(ds_name: str, pmids: list[str]) -> deeplake.Dataset:\n",
        "    schema = {\n",
        "        'pmid':  \"int32\",\n",
        "        'title': Text(index_type=BM25),\n",
        "        'abstract': Text(index_type=BM25),\n",
        "        'payload': Dict(),          # full XML for anything else you may need later\n",
        "        'embedding': Embedding(1024),\n",
        "    }\n",
        "\n",
        "    if deeplake.exists(ds_name):\n",
        "        deeplake.delete(ds_name)\n",
        "    ds = deeplake.create(ds_name, schema=schema)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # --- search PubMed (example: last 20 y; retmax can be cranked up) ---\n",
        "    q = {\n",
        "        \"db\": \"pubmed\",\n",
        "        \"term\": \"2005:2025[dp]\",   # date‑published range\n",
        "        \"retmax\": 100,             # adjust higher for full crawl\n",
        "        \"retmode\": \"json\"\n",
        "    }\n",
        "    ids = requests.get(\"https://eutils.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/eutils/esearch.fcgi\",\n",
        "                    params=q).json()[\"esearchresult\"][\"idlist\"]\n",
        "\n",
        "    for pmid in tqdm(ids):\n",
        "        xml = requests.get(\"https://eutils.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/eutils/efetch.fcgi\",\n",
        "                        params={\"db\":\"pubmed\",\"id\":pmid,\"retmode\":\"xml\"}).text\n",
        "\n",
        "        try:\n",
        "            root = ET.fromstring(xml)\n",
        "        except ET.ParseError as e:\n",
        "            continue\n",
        "\n",
        "        article = root.find(\".//Article\")\n",
        "        if article is not None:\n",
        "            title = article.findtext(\".//ArticleTitle\", default=\"\")\n",
        "            abstract  = \" \".join([t.text or \"\" for t in article.findall(\".//AbstractText\")])\n",
        "            ds.append([{\n",
        "                \"pmid\": int(pmid),\n",
        "                \"title\": title,\n",
        "                \"abstract\": abstract,\n",
        "                \"payload\": {\"xml\": xml},      # keep raw for later mining\n",
        "                \"embedding\": generator.generate_embeddings(text=title + \":\" +  abstract)[\"text_embedding\"]\n",
        "            }])\n",
        "    ds.commit()\n",
        "    return ds\n",
        "\n",
        "pubmed = create_pubmed_table(f\"{lakehouse_s3}/pubmed\", ['100','101','102','103','104'])\n",
        "pubmed.summary()"
      ]
    },

        "import requests, textwrap, deeplake\n",
        "from deeplake.types import Text, BM25, Dict, Embedding\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "def create_genbank_table(ds_name: str, retmax: int = 100) -> deeplake.Dataset:\n",
        "    schema = {\n",
        "        'accession': Text(index_type=BM25),\n",
        "        'definition': Text(index_type=BM25),\n",
        "        'sequence': Text(),\n",
        "        'payload': Dict(),\n",
        "        'embedding': Embedding(1024)\n",
        "    }\n",
        "\n",
        "    if deeplake.exists(ds_name):\n",
        "        deeplake.delete(ds_name)\n",
        "    ds = deeplake.create(ds_name, schema=schema)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # --- search GenBank (nuccore) ---\n",
        "    q = {\"db\":\"nuccore\", \"term\":\"biomol_genomic[PROP]\", \"retmax\":100, \"retmode\":\"json\"}\n",
        "    ids = requests.get(\"https://eutils.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/eutils/esearch.fcgi\",\n",
        "                    params=q).json()[\"esearchresult\"][\"idlist\"]\n",
        "\n",
        "    for acc in tqdm(ids):\n",
        "        rec = requests.get(\"https://eutils.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/entrez/eutils/efetch.fcgi\",\n",
        "                        params={\"db\":\"nuccore\",\"id\":acc,\"rettype\":\"gbwithparts\",\"retmode\":\"text\"}).text\n",
        "        # VERY crude extraction\n",
        "        defline, *body = rec.splitlines()\n",
        "        definition = defline.partition(\"  \")[2].strip()\n",
        "        sequence = \"\".join(line.strip() for line in body if line and line[0].isdigit()==False)\n",
        "\n",
        "        ds.append([{\n",
        "            \"accession\": acc,\n",
        "            \"definition\": definition,\n",
        "            \"sequence\": '\\n'.join(textwrap.wrap(sequence, 60)),\n",
        "            \"payload\": rec,\n",
        "            \"embedding\": generator.generate_embeddings(text=acc + \":\" +  definition + \":\" + str(rec))[\"text_embedding\"]\n",
        "        }])\n",
        "    ds.commit()\n",
        "    return ds\n",
        "\n",
        "genbank = create_genbank_table(f\"{lakehouse_s3}/genbank_nuccore\")\n",
        "genbank.summary()"

        "import io, zipfile, requests, PIL.Image as Image, deeplake\n",
        "from deeplake.types import Image as DLImage, Dict, Embedding\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "\n",
        "def create_bbbc_images_table(ds_name: str) -> deeplake.Dataset:\n",
        "\n",
        "    schema = {\n",
        "        'image': DLImage(),      # stored natively; auto‑compressed\n",
        "        'meta':  Dict(),         # plate, well, etc.\n",
        "        'embedding': Embedding(1024)\n",
        "    }\n",
        "\n",
        "    if deeplake.exists(ds_name):\n",
        "        deeplake.delete(ds_name)\n",
        "    ds = deeplake.create(ds_name, schema=schema)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # --- download one canonical BBBC set; swap URL for others (Cell Painting, RxRx, etc.) ---\n",
        "    url = \"https://data.broadinstitute.org/bbbc/BBBC001/BBBC001_v1_images_tif.zip\"\n",
        "    zbytes = requests.get(url, stream=True).content\n",
        "    with zipfile.ZipFile(io.BytesIO(zbytes)) as zf:\n",
        "        for fname in zf.namelist():\n",
        "            if not fname.lower().endswith((\".png\",\".tif\",\".tiff\",\".jpg\")):\n",
        "                continue\n",
        "            img = Image.open(zf.open(fname)).convert(\"RGB\")\n",
        "            plate, well = fname.split('/')[-2:]  # simple metadata\n",
        "            ds.append([{\n",
        "                \"image\": np.array(img),\n",
        "                \"meta\": {\"source\":\"BBBC004\", \"filename\": fname, \"plate\": plate, \"well\": well},\n",
        "                \"embedding\": generator.generate_embeddings(img=img)[\"image_embedding\"]\n",
        "            }])\n",
        "    ds.commit()\n",
        "    return ds\n",
        "\n",
        "bbbc = create_bbbc_images_table(f\"{lakehouse_s3}/bbbc_images\")\n",
        "bbbc.summary()"
      ]
    },

        "def lexical_search_pubchem(query: str, top_k: int = 3):\n",
        "    \"\"\" Searches PubChem with Lexical Index using BM25 \"\"\"\n",
        "    query = f\"\"\"\n",
        "        SELECT *, ROW_NUMBER() as row_id\n",
        "        ORDER BY BM25_SIMILARITY(title, '{query}') DESC\n",
        "        LIMIT {top_k}\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    pubchem.refresh()\n",
        "    results = pubchem.query(query)\n",
        "    return [str(r['title'] + \":\" + r['description']) + ':' + str(r['payload']) for r in results]\n",
        "\n",
        "lexical_search_pubchem('cancer', top_k = 1)"
      ]
    },

        "def embedding_search_pubmed(query: str, top_k: int = 3):\n",
        "    \"\"\" Searches Pubmed using vectors \"\"\"\n",
        "    arr = generator.generate_embeddings(text=query)[\"text_embedding\"]\n",
        "    text_vector = ','.join(str(x) for x in arr)\n",
        "\n",
        "    query = f\"\"\"\n",
        "        SELECT *, ROW_NUMBER() as row_id\n",
        "        ORDER BY COSINE_SIMILARITY(embedding, ARRAY[{text_vector}]) DESC\n",
        "        LIMIT {top_k}\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    results = pubmed.query(query)\n",
        "    return [str(r['title']) + ':' + str(r['abstract']) for r in results]\n",
        "\n",
        "embedding_search_pubmed('cancer')"
      ]
    },

        "import math\n",
        "import numpy as np\n",
        "from typing import Any, Dict, List, Optional\n",
        "from pydantic import BaseModel\n",
        "\n",
        "# combine hybrid search results\n",
        "class Document(BaseModel):\n",
        "    id: str\n",
        "    data: str\n",
        "    score: Optional[float] = None\n",
        "\n",
        "def documentify(results, scores) -> Dict[str, Document]:\n",
        "    docs = {}\n",
        "    for el, score in zip(results, scores):\n",
        "        docs[str(el[\"row_id\"])] = Document(\n",
        "            id=str(el[\"row_id\"]),\n",
        "            data=str(el['payload']) + \":\" + el['sequence'] + \":\" + el['accession'] + el['definition'],\n",
        "            score=score\n",
        "        )\n",
        "    return docs\n",
        "\n",
        "def softmax(retrieved_score: list[float], max_weight: int = 700) -> Dict[str, Document]:\n",
        "    # Compute the exponentials\n",
        "    exp_scores = [math.exp(min(score, max_weight)) for score in retrieved_score]\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Compute the sum of the exponentials\n",
        "    sum_exp_scores = sum(exp_scores)\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Update the scores of the documents using softmax\n",
        "    new_weights = []\n",
        "    for score in exp_scores:\n",
        "        new_weights.append(score / sum_exp_scores)\n",
        "\n",
        "    return new_weights\n",
        "\n",
        "def fusion(docs_vs: Dict[str, Document], docs_bm25: Dict[str, Document], VECTOR_WEIGHT = 0.5) -> Dict[str, Document]:\n",
        "\n",
        "    LEXICAL_WEIGHT = 1-VECTOR_WEIGHT\n",
        "\n",
        "    results: Dict[str, Dict[str, Document]] = {}\n",
        "\n",
        "    for k in set(docs_vs) | set(docs_bm25):\n",
        "        results[k] = docs_vs.get(k, None) or docs_bm25.get(k, None)\n",
        "        vs_score = VECTOR_WEIGHT * docs_vs[k].score if k in docs_vs else 0\n",
        "        bm_score = LEXICAL_WEIGHT * docs_bm25[k].score if k in docs_bm25 else 0\n",
        "        results[k].score = vs_score + bm_score\n",
        "\n",
        "    return results\n",
        "\n",
        "def hybrid_search_genbank(query: str, top_k: int = 3):\n",
        "    \"\"\" Searches both using lexical + vector indexes and returns combined resutl\"\"\"\n",
        "    arr = generator.generate_embeddings(text=query)[\"text_embedding\"]\n",
        "    embedding_string = ','.join(str(x) for x in arr)\n",
        "\n",
        "    tql_vs = f\"\"\"\n",
        "        SELECT *, cosine_similarity(embedding, ARRAY[{embedding_string}]) as score\n",
        "        FROM (\n",
        "            SELECT *, ROW_NUMBER() AS row_id\n",
        "        )\n",
        "        ORDER BY cosine_similarity(embedding, ARRAY[{embedding_string}]) DESC\n",
        "        LIMIT {top_k}\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "\n",
        "    tql_bm25 = f\"\"\"\n",
        "        SELECT *, BM25_SIMILARITY(definition, '{query}') as score\n",
        "        FROM (\n",
        "            SELECT *, ROW_NUMBER() AS row_id\n",
        "        )\n",
        "        ORDER BY BM25_SIMILARITY(definition, '{query}') DESC\n",
        "        LIMIT {top_k}\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    vs_results = genbank.query(tql_vs)\n",
        "    bm25_results = genbank.query(tql_bm25)\n",
        "\n",
        "    vs_score = softmax(vs_results[\"score\"])\n",
        "    bm_score = softmax(bm25_results[\"score\"])\n",
        "\n",
        "    docs_vs = documentify(vs_results, vs_score)\n",
        "    docs_bm25 = documentify(bm25_results, bm_score)\n",
        "\n",
        "    results = fusion(docs_vs, docs_bm25)\n",
        "    results = list(sorted(results.items(), key=lambda item: item[1].score, reverse=True))\n",
        "    return results[:top_k]\n",
        "\n",
        "\n",
        "genbank.summary()\n",
        "hybrid_search_genbank(query=\"cancer DNA\")[0]\n"
      ]
    },

        "import base64\n",
        "from io import BytesIO\n",
        "from PIL import Image\n",
        "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
        "\n",
        "def visual_search_bbbc(query: str, top_k: int = 1):\n",
        "    \"\"\" Visual Search in BBBC and returns the image with metadata \"\"\"\n",
        "    arr = generator.generate_embeddings(text=query)[\"text_embedding\"]\n",
        "    text_vector = ','.join(str(x) for x in arr)\n",
        "\n",
        "    query = f\"\"\"\n",
        "        SELECT *, ROW_NUMBER() as row_id\n",
        "        ORDER BY COSINE_SIMILARITY(embedding, ARRAY[{text_vector}]) DESC\n",
        "        LIMIT {top_k}\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    results = bbbc.query(query)\n",
        "\n",
        "    def to_base64_png(arr: np.ndarray) -> tuple[str, str]:\n",
        "        if arr.dtype != np.uint8:\n",
        "            arr = arr.astype(np.uint8)\n",
        "        img = Image.fromarray(arr)          # arr must be H×W×3 or H×W\n",
        "        buf = io.BytesIO()\n",
        "        img.save(buf, format=\"PNG\")\n",
        "        return base64.b64encode(buf.getvalue()).decode(), \"image/png\"\n",
        "\n",
        "    return [(to_base64_png(r['image']), str(r['meta'])) for r in results]\n",
        "\n",
        "query = 'GLP-1 receptor colon cancer'\n",
        "\n",
        "b64_str = visual_search_bbbc(query)[0][0][0]\n",
        "img = Image.open(BytesIO(base64.b64decode(b64_str)))\n",
        "\n",
        "plt.imshow(img)\n",
        "plt.axis('off')\n",
        "plt.show()\n"
      ]
    },

        "import boto3\n",
        "import json\n",
        "\n",
        "def query_candidate_with_llm(query: str, model_id = \"anthropic.claude-3-5-sonnet-20240620-v1:0\"):\n",
        "    bedrock_runtime = boto3.client('bedrock-runtime', region_name='us-east-1')\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Define your prompt\n",
        "    system_prompt = \"\"\"\n",
        "        You are an expert Drug Discovery candidate answer provider.\n",
        "        You have access to PubMed, PubChem, GenBank and BBBC\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "    (b64, mime), meta = visual_search_bbbc(query, top_k = 1)[0]\n",
        "    prompt = f\"\"\"Here is the user query: {query}\n",
        "\n",
        "    Here are retrieved results from\n",
        "        PubChem: {hybrid_search_genbank(query, top_k=3)}\n",
        "        BBBC: {meta} with image attached\n",
        "        PubMed: {embedding_search_pubmed(query, top_k=3)}\n",
        "        GenBank: {hybrid_search_genbank(query, top_k=3)}\n",
        "    \"\"\"\n",
        "\n",
        "    # Prepare the request body\n",
        "    request_body = {\n",
        "        \"anthropic_version\": \"bedrock-2023-05-31\",\n",
        "        \"system\": system_prompt,\n",
        "        \"messages\": [\n",
        "            {\n",
        "                \"role\": \"user\",\n",
        "                \"content\": [\n",
        "                    {\n",
        "                        \"type\": \"text\",\n",
        "                        \"text\": prompt\n",
        "                    },\n",
        "                    {\n",
        "                        \"type\": \"image\",\n",
        "                        \"source\": {\"type\": \"base64\", \"media_type\": mime, \"data\": b64}\n",
        "                    }\n",
        "                ]\n",
        "            }\n",
        "        ],\n",
        "        \"max_tokens\": 512,\n",
        "        \"temperature\": 0.7,\n",
        "        \"top_p\": 1\n",
        "    }\n",
        "\n",
        "    try:\n",
        "        # Call the model\n",
        "        response = bedrock_runtime.invoke_model(\n",
        "            modelId=model_id,\n",
        "            body=json.dumps(request_body),\n",
        "        )\n",
        "\n",
        "        # Parse and print the response\n",
        "        response_body = json.loads(response['body'].read())\n",
        "        print(response_body['content'][0]['text'])\n",
        "\n",
        "    except Exception as e:\n",
        "        print(f\"An error occurred: {str(e)}\")"
      ]
    },
